To terminate a C program, you can use the `exit()` function from the `stdlib.h` library. This function allows you to end the execution of the program immediately. Here's an example of how to use it:

```c
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    // Your code here

    exit(0);
}
```

By calling `exit(0)`, the program will terminate and return a status code of 0, indicating successful execution.

